title: Czech zoo celebrates birth of cheetah quins
description:
(3 Aug 2017) Prague Zoo said on Thursday five cheetah cubs recently born at the park are doing well.
The quintuplets - three males and two female - have survived the most critical period after their birth on 15 May.
Their mother, six-year-old Savannah, is taking good care of them, according to zoo officials.
It was the second litter for Savannah as she gave birth to quadruplets in 2014. 
In both cases, five-year-old Ben was the father. 
The cubs have not been named yet. 
Visitors will have the first chance to see them on 26 August.
Cheetahs are the fastest animals on land but also are vulnerable to various diseases. 
Scientists say every cub is critical to saving the species, which is threatened with extinction in the wild.
